The following code block replaces the target sorry with a proof. The proof utilizes the fact that for a submartingale $X$, the positive part $X^+$ is a submartingale, and thus $X_\tau^+ \le \mathbb{E}[X_n^+ \mid \mathcal{F}_\tau]$. Since the family $\{\mathbb{E}[X_n^+ \mid \mathcal{F}_\tau]\}_\tau$ is uniformly integrable (being conditional expectations of an integrable random variable), $\{X_\tau^+\}$ is uniformly integrable. For a submartingale with bounded stopping times, this implies uniform integrability of the stopped process.

